# SwiftUI Conventions

## View structure

- One primary `struct …: View` per screen file; small private helpers below or in `SharedUI.swift`.
- Read app state with `@EnvironmentObject var app: AppState` — do not create a second `AppState`.
- Local ephemeral UI only: `@State` (e.g. appear animations). Persist flow/nav in `AppState`.

```swift
struct SomeView: View {
    @EnvironmentObject var app: AppState
    @State private var appear = false

    var body: some View {
        ZStack {
            GGColor.black.ignoresSafeArea()
            // content
        }
        .onAppear { withAnimation(.easeOut(duration: 0.8)) { appear = true } }
    }
}
```

## Interaction & animation

- Buttons: wrap labels with `.buttonStyle(PressableStyle())` for press scale/opacity.
- Tab / phase changes: `withAnimation(.easeOut(duration: 0.2))` or `.easeInOut(duration: 0.35)`.
- Immersive watch Shorts: tab bar uses `ghosted: app.isImmersive` — don't show a second chrome.

## Shared pieces

- Post action row → `PostActions`
- Watch Feed/Shorts/TV control → `WatchSegments(selection: $app.watchSubFeed)`
- Onboarding question chrome → `MadeleineBubble` + `ProgressDots` in `Auth/`

## Models

- Domain types are simple structs (`Identifiable` with `let id = UUID()`).
- Don't rename `GG*` tokens or strip source-compat aliases in `Theme.swift` without need.
- Prefer SF Symbols for icons (`house`, `play.rectangle`, `bag`, `magnifyingglass`, `sparkles`).
